task.summary: Automated the import of images and names. Made some of the code more readable. Also added some prints for debugging purposes.

Moved the flask_face_recog.py, the Mugshots and the Models to the flask folder, so we could flash the results to the web page. Also I changed a little the app.py code to flash the comparisons, commented out the redirection line to "thank-you.html".
Also I created a global variable for tolerance, so we could tweak it in ad-hoc. I reduced the tolerance to 0.5 as Tyler was identified as someone else, so I dropped the tolerance to 0.5 units from 0.6. Better resolution on the photos may solve the problem with higher tolerances.
Added some code to save the images as numpy arrays, needs to be fixed as it raises an exception
